review_blob: Dark porter with a nutty caramel aroma, the palate is caramel, with roasted malt, liquorice, and slightly bitter very nutty finish. Not bad.
beer_name: Dia De Los Muertos Pay The Ferryman Porter

review_blob: This was never going to be a classic. Golden lager, grainy stale aroma, malty grainy flavour, quite watery, light slightly metallic finish.

Dark crimson ale, a nutty chocolate aroma, a chocolate roasted malt flavour with a background of berry fruit. The finish is dryish but fruity, this is a very drinkable tasty ale, just what a modern mild should be.
Orange cloudy ale, hoppy grainy aroma, biscuit malt flavour with citrous undertones. The finish is gently hopped and a little light, but overall quite pleasant.

Blonde ale with a pronounced herbal lavender aroma, the flavour is herbal, malty, with lightly hopped finish. This is a fine example of the genre, it has all the summery feel of a Belgian blonde, the name is well chosen.
Pale golden ale, aroma is stale hops , a lemony citrous flavour with a bitterish saline finish. There is not much hop character here, and I dont find it terribly sophisticated or pleasant.
Dark stout with an earthy fruity aroma, roasted malt cranberry bitter flavour, berry earthy finish, quite a subtle ale.
Pale golden ale with a herbal yeasty aroma, herbal flavour, slightly citrous, lightly hopped finish, pleasant light beer.
Dark brown rauchbier with a smoky bacon aroma, a malty caramel flavour with bacon undertone. The finish is rather light but this is a pleasant and tasty smoked beer.
Pale pink fruit beer with an intense fruity aroma, a light raspberry flavour, very weak and watery, no finish to speak of. Someone buy these guys a plane ticket to Belgium.
Pale red fruit beer with a light raspberry aroma, light carbonated raspberry flavour, weak watery finish. This is far too weak for its strength.
Dark crimson ale with a berry aroma, flavour of berries and caramel sugar, warming dry finish. Some spiciness but lacking in flavour
Golden ale with a resinous aroma, fruity grapefruit flavour with a bitterish fruity finish. Refreshing but nothing special.
Cloudy crimson fruit beer, strawberry aroma, flavour of berries with a light slightly watery finish.
beer_name: Van Bulck Organic Wild Fruit Beer

review_blob: Dark stout with a milk chocolate aroma, the palate is cocoa, chocolate and vanilla, a lightly bitter finish. A little sweet and cloying for my palate, but the strength of this beer is well disguised.
Dark Xmas ale with a roasted malt aroma, palate of berry fruit and coffee, rich an d fruity with a warming spicy finish. Very nice.
Golden ale with a citrous aroma, lemon corpus flavour with a gentle bitter finish. Light but refreshing.
beer_name: Treboom Yorkshire Sparkle Really Pale Ale

review_blob: Dark weizenbock style beer, coffee and roasted malt aroma. The flavour Is fruity but heavily roasted malt, a dry bitter warming finish. This is a very original beers from the pioneers of the craft movement.
Dark porter beer with a plummy aroma, a fruity plummy spiced flavour, with adryish bitter finish. A typically distinctive beer from titanic.
Dark Xmas ale, plummy fruit aroma, palate is caramel fruitiness, a dry finish with some bitterness, for me it lacks richness and spiciness, pleasant but underpowered.

This is a beefed up biere de garde for the festive season, deep golden in colour, aroma of sweetmalt and spices. The palate is sweet caramel malt with a spicy background and warming dry finish. A subtle and very pleasant beer from northern France.
Dark Christmas ale, aroma of marzipan, fruitcake. A sweet palate of berry fruit and a dryish fruity finish. Lacking the rich complexity of the best seasonal beers, and a little too sweet, not bad.

A cloudy Orange american pale ale. The aroma is peachy, the palate is bitter oranges. The finish is well balanced bitter hops. Not sensational by any means, but very refreshing and the sign of another high quality London brewery.
beer_name: London Beer Factory Paxton Pale Ale

review_blob: A cloudy yellow wit beer with a subtle citrous aroma. The flavour Is citric, finish rather weak and lacking in floral or herbal notes
Dark Xmas ale, the aroma is a gorgeous array of red fruit and spice. The palate is very sweet, flavours of plum and dates, a warming finish, lacking a little in spice. Pretty good.
Dark stout, roasted malt aroma. The palate is rather sweet and fruity and the finish is dryish and bitter. Not bad.

I am rating this as press gangs arrival from the Baytown brewery near Whitby. A cloudy Orange ale with a toffee malt aroma, the flavour is malty with some fruitiness, but the flavour drips away and the finish is weak. Not enough hop impact here.
Dark ale with raisin and berry aroma. The palate is berry with a dry hopped finish. This is pleasant but a little underpowered for a seasonal ale.

A pale amber ale, slightly cloudy, with a perfumed fruity aroma. The palate is earthy maltiness with a very salty bitterness. This is a very interesting version of an ipa with the hop finish dry and astringent, a brewery unknown to me and worth further investigation. I bought this on a day trip to lille, look forward to going back.

Dark amber ale with a bready toasted cinnamon aroma. The flavour Is dark fruit, toasted malt, with a dry finish, slightly warming. This is pleasant but lacks the richness and spiciness of the best Belgian Xmas ales.
beer_name: Saint Germain Page 24 Bire de Noel

review_blob: Pale amber ale with a floral aroma. The palate is zesty maltiness with a hint of apple, the finish is bitter hopped but lacking a little depth. This is a nice take on a Kentish ale, the hops are a little bit muted, but quite pleasant.
Orange ale, breast aroma with pine residue, there is fruitiness and toasty malt in the palate, and a deep hopped finish. A west coast ipa to savour.
Dark golden pilsner, bready, grassy aroma, sweet malty flavour and a bitter hopped finish. A rather well balanced example of the genre, fresh and tasty.
Golden ale with a hippy yeasty aroma. The flavour Is fruity citrous leading to a very bitter hopped finish. This carries a decent punch for a light ale from a new brewery showing lots of promise.
Dark golden cloudy pale ale, pronounced mango and peach aroma and biscuity malt. Grapefruit and mango flavour, bitter hopped finish. Very tasty indeed.
Cloudy pale golden ale, yeasty aroma, weak carbonated flavour, lightly hopped finish. This is tasteless and entirely lacking in flavour, not very good.
Pale golden ale, well hopped aroma, there is a grapefruit undertone to the malty palate, the finish is hopped but slightly metallic. Not unpleasant, but it doesnt win any awards for me.
Dark ale with a toffee aroma, the flavour is toffee an treacle with a fetish slightly hopped finish. Nicely done, although it is inevitably rather cloying.
Hazy amber ale, tea aroma, malty flavour with some fruitiness, an earthy finish. Interesting to find a traditional British ale of this kind from southern Spain, but nothing special really
Cloudy amber ale, pine aroma, a malty flavour with a citrous undertone and a lightly hopped but earthy finish. A very traditional bitter and none the worse for that.
Golden ale with a piney citrous aroma, fruity creamy flavour, just a little flat, slightly bitter, rather light finish. It does have a pleasant creamy feel, but not a big impact.
Pale golden pilsner, apple aroma, light malty flavour, lightly hopped finish. A rather insubstantial and weak brew.

Pale golden ale with a very large head, lemony aroma, pithy fruit flavour with a dry bitter finish. I am disinclined to criticize the slight lack of depth as I take the view that low alcohol ales such as this one should be encouraged for the sake of variety, although for my part there is too much carbonation. Quite pleasant.

Cloudy Orange pale ale, hoppy citrous aroma, fruity pine flavour with a well hopped bitter finish. There is a slight lack of depth to the finish, but on the whole this is a pleasant pale ale with flavour belying its strength.
Pale amber ale, with a light citrous aroma, malty flavour with a bitter rather antiseptic finish. Citrous undertones are pleasant, but the aftertaste is not pleasant.

Cloudy Orange weiss beer, the aroma is of grains and hops, flavour of banana with a pronounced bitter hopped finish. Enjoyed this because while there is the spicy fruitiness of a weiss beer, there is also the dry hopped character of an ipa. The inventiveness shown by this brewery is quite something.
Pale amber pale ale, pine and fruity aroma. The flavour Is Orange fruit with a bitter undertone and an astringent hoppy finish. Not bad.
Golden wit bier without a head, appley floral aroma, flavour of apple, ginger, cloves and vanilla. Not unpleasant but entirely lacking in depth or finish.
Porter with a dark crimson colour, stale coffee aroma, plum liquorice flavour with a dry bitter finish. Pleasant, not spectacular, a little lacking in depth for a genuine porter, supermarket beer.
beer_name: Lidl Hatherwood The Purple Panther Porter No.5

review_blob: Great name, great beer. Cloudy dark Orange in colour, pine and Orange aroma, a fresh flavour of line and tropical fruit. The finish is hoppy and dry, a really tasty beer from the can
